Product Name: Lenovo Th30 Bluetooth Headphone Gaming Low Latency Music Noise Reduction Smart Touch With Mic Bluetooth 5.1
Comments:
Best Feature(s): cushion of earmuffs
Performance: decent, quite good for its price
Value For Money: yes, you get what you pay for
- Earmuff : sizing quite average, maybe slightly larger than normal but ppl w larger ears might find them slightly uncomfy. / cushion rly soft, really comfortable for longer durations of wearing. (I got large ears but they feel much much more comfortable than other headphones I've tried! won't cover your ears fully but the cushion is REALLY soft, i love it 🤩) ppl with smaller ears don't need to worry, most likely will cover ur ears one 👍🏻

- Sound : decent, not the best if you're looking for strong bass and stuff. / Sound does not leak! but if you blast full volume then ofc will leak. I tried covering earmuffs while blasting music, cnnt rly hear. The sound cnnt rly penetrate through the plastic unless you rest ur ear directly on it (taking public transport or at library shld not be a problem 👌🏻) / Volume of the headphones might be very low at first but you can max out the volume on the headphones and the sound shld be fine frm there! / Sound gets muffled at times but goes back to normal again. very weird but it's like that ig :/

- Wearing duration comfort : Larger ears can start to feel pain earlier (for me i feel pain aft 3hrs of constant wearing but few minutes rest can wear agn) BUT not heavy! super lightweight, mayb ppl with larger heads might find them clamping your head tgt. My head not v small and it's still quite comfortable 👍🏻 
(Earmuff hole about 5.5cm) 

- Battery Life : Quite okay, doesn't run out very fast. If full charge can last up to 8 hrs mayb (constant usage) battery doesn't drain too fast. 

- Aesthetic Qualities : Looks rly nice, the beige is subtle like cream latte typa vibes! / Shape of the headphones looks clean and simple, no bulges on the sides of the headphones if you don't like it bulky 

- Overall : Very worth the buy for starter headphones js for casual usage! price super reasonable for the quality of product 👌🏻 It's worth the try, seems like these headphones wld last quite long, the quality doesn't seem like won't last more than half a year 👌🏻

Product Name: Lenovo TH30 Bluetooth Headphone Wireless Headphone Gaming Low Latency Music Noise Reduction Smart Touch With Mic Bluetooth 5.1
Comments:
Best Feature(s): cushion of earmuffs
Performance: decent, quite good for its price
Value For Money: yes, you get what you pay for
- Earmuff : sizing quite average, maybe slightly larger than normal but ppl w larger ears might find them slightly uncomfy. / cushion rly soft, really comfortable for longer durations of wearing. (I got large ears but they feel much much more comfortable than other headphones I've tried! won't cover your ears fully but the cushion is REALLY soft, i love it 🤩) ppl with smaller ears don't need to worry, most likely will cover ur ears one 👍🏻

- Sound : decent, not the best if you're looking for strong bass and stuff. / Sound does not leak! but if you blast full volume then ofc will leak. I tried covering earmuffs while blasting music, cnnt rly hear. The sound cnnt rly penetrate through the plastic unless you rest ur ear directly on it (taking public transport or at library shld not be a problem 👌🏻) / Volume of the headphones might be very low at first but you can max out the volume on the headphones and the sound shld be fine frm there! / Sound gets muffled at times but goes back to normal again. very weird but it's like that ig :/

- Wearing duration comfort : Larger ears can start to feel pain earlier (for me i feel pain aft 3hrs of constant wearing but few minutes rest can wear agn) BUT not heavy! super lightweight, mayb ppl with larger heads might find them clamping your head tgt. My head not v small and it's still quite comfortable 👍🏻 
(Earmuff hole about 5.5cm) 

- Battery Life : Quite okay, doesn't run out very fast. If full charge can last up to 8 hrs mayb (constant usage) battery doesn't drain too fast. 

- Aesthetic Qualities : Looks rly nice, the beige is subtle like cream latte typa vibes! / Shape of the headphones looks clean and simple, no bulges on the sides of the headphones if you don't like it bulky 

- Overall : Very worth the buy for starter headphones js for casual usage! price super reasonable for the quality of product 👌🏻 It's worth the try, seems like these headphones wld last quite long, the quality doesn't seem like won't last more than half a year 👌🏻
